      "If you have been researching ways to customise your laptop in Lusaka, you have probably encountered the terms laptop wrap, laptop skin, and laptop sticker used somewhat interchangeably. They are not the same thing. Here is the clear distinction between all three — and why what The Custom ZM produces is in a different category from the others.",
      "**Laptop Stickers**",
      "A laptop sticker is exactly what it sounds like — an adhesive sticker applied to the surface of your laptop. Stickers are small, they do not cover full surfaces, they leave gaps and inconsistent coverage, and they rarely look intentional. Stickers are inexpensive and show it. They peel at the edges. They bubble. They leave residue when removed. Most importantly, they do not create a coherent visual identity — they create a collage of random imagery that looks like an afterthought.",
