      "**Laptop Skins**",
      "A laptop skin is a full-surface adhesive vinyl sheet designed to cover a large portion of a laptop's surface — typically the top cover. The quality difference between a sticker and a skin is significant — skins are precision cut, cover full surfaces, and are printed at a level that looks intentional. However, most laptop skins in the market are self-applied, meaning the installation quality depends on the person applying them. Bubbles, misalignment, and edge lifting are common when self-applied.",
      "**Laptop Wraps — What The Custom ZM Produces**",
      "A laptop wrap at The Custom ZM is a professional-grade full surface vinyl treatment, precision cut to your exact laptop model dimensions, printed at high resolution, and applied by our team at our studio. It is not a self-applied sheet. It is a professionally installed surface transformation.",
